# Example BetterStack status-page webhook gate (fork-only firstmate feature).
#
# Copy this file to config/betterstack-webhook.env (gitignored, local) to OPT IN.
# Presence of that file is the whole gate: with it, firstmate wires the inbox
# poll and shares the ClickStack receiver's listener process on this route;
# without it, the route is completely inert (404).
#
# Unlike ClickStack, leave BETTERSTACK_WEBHOOK_TOKEN empty (or omit it): running
# bin/fm-betterstack-arm.sh generates and persists an unguessable token into this
# file the first time it runs. There is no safe default with no token, because a
# BetterStack status-page webhook subscription cannot send a custom auth header
# (see docs/betterstack-webhook.md) - the URL query token is the only guard.
#
# See docs/betterstack-webhook.md for the full mechanism, lifecycle, and how to
# retrieve the generated token to build the subscription URL.

BETTERSTACK_WEBHOOK_TOKEN=
